61String AutomationCommandError::toProtocolString()
62{
63 String protocolErrorName = Inspector::Protocol::AutomationHelpers::getEnumConstantValue(type);
64 if (!message)
65 return protocolErrorName;
66 return makeString(protocolErrorName, errorNameAndDetailsSeparator, *message);
67}

70// https://www.w3.org/TR/webdriver/#dfn-session-page-load-timeout
71static const Seconds defaultPageLoadTimeout = 300_s;
72// https://www.w3.org/TR/webdriver/#dfn-page-loading-strategy

75WebAutomationSession::WebAutomationSession()
76 : m_client(makeUnique<API::AutomationSessionClient>())
77 , m_frontendRouter(FrontendRouter::create())
78 , m_backendDispatcher(BackendDispatcher::create(m_frontendRouter.copyRef()))
79 , m_domainDispatcher(AutomationBackendDispatcher::create(m_backendDispatcher, this))
80 , m_domainNotifier(makeUnique<AutomationFrontendDispatcher>(m_frontendRouter))
81 , m_loadTimer(RunLoop::main(), this, &WebAutomationSession::loadTimerFired)
82{
83}

85WebAutomationSession::~WebAutomationSession()
86{
87 ASSERT(!m_client);
88 ASSERT(!m_processPool);
89}

91void WebAutomationSession::setClient(std::unique_ptr<API::AutomationSessionClient>&& client)
92{
93 m_client = WTFMove(client);
94}

96void WebAutomationSession::setProcessPool(WebKit::WebProcessPool* processPool)
97{
98 if (m_processPool)
99 m_processPool->removeMessageReceiver(Messages::WebAutomationSession::messageReceiverName());
100
101 m_processPool = processPool;
102
103 if (m_processPool)
104 m_processPool->addMessageReceiver(Messages::WebAutomationSession::messageReceiverName(), *this);
105}

119void WebAutomationSession::connect(Inspector::FrontendChannel& channel, bool isAutomaticConnection, bool immediatelyPause)
120{
121 UNUSED_PARAM(isAutomaticConnection);
122 UNUSED_PARAM(immediatelyPause);
123
124 m_remoteChannel = &channel;
125 m_frontendRouter->connectFrontend(channel);
126
127 setIsPaired(true);
128}
129
130void WebAutomationSession::disconnect(Inspector::FrontendChannel& channel)
131{
132 ASSERT(&channel == m_remoteChannel);
133 terminate();
134}
135
136#endif // ENABLE(REMOTE_INSPECTOR)
137
138void WebAutomationSession::terminate()
139{
140#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
141 for (auto& identifier : copyToVector(m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.keys())) {
142 auto callback = m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(identifier);
143 callback(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(InternalError));
144 }
145#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
146
147#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
148 for (auto& identifier : copyToVector(m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.keys())) {
149 auto callback = m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(identifier);
150 callback(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(InternalError));
151 }
152#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
153
154#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_WHEEL_INTERACTIONS)
155 for (auto& identifier : copyToVector(m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.keys())) {
156 auto callback = m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(identifier);
157 callback(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(InternalError));
158 }
159#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_WHEEL_INTERACTIONS)
160
161#if ENABLE(REMOTE_INSPECTOR)
162 if (Inspector::FrontendChannel* channel = m_remoteChannel) {
163 m_remoteChannel = nullptr;
164 m_frontendRouter->disconnectFrontend(*channel);
165 }
166
167 setIsPaired(false);
168#endif
169
170 if (m_client)
171 m_client->didDisconnectFromRemote(*this);
172}
173
174WebPageProxy* WebAutomationSession::webPageProxyForHandle(const String& handle)
175{
176 auto iter = m_handleWebPageMap.find(handle);
177 if (iter == m_handleWebPageMap.end())
178 return nullptr;
179 return WebProcessProxy::webPage(iter->value);
180}
181
182String WebAutomationSession::handleForWebPageProxy(const WebPageProxy& webPageProxy)
183{
184 auto iter = m_webPageHandleMap.find(webPageProxy.identifier());
185 if (iter != m_webPageHandleMap.end())
186 return iter->value;
187
188 String handle = "page-" + createCanonicalUUIDString().convertToASCIIUppercase();
189
190 auto firstAddResult = m_webPageHandleMap.add(webPageProxy.identifier(), handle);
191 RELEASE_ASSERT(firstAddResult.isNewEntry);
192
193 auto secondAddResult = m_handleWebPageMap.add(handle, webPageProxy.identifier());
194 RELEASE_ASSERT(secondAddResult.isNewEntry);
195
196 return handle;
197}
198
199void WebAutomationSession::didDestroyFrame(FrameIdentifier frameID)
200{
201 auto handle = m_webFrameHandleMap.take(frameID);
202 if (!handle.isEmpty())
203 m_handleWebFrameMap.remove(handle);
204}
205
206std::optional<FrameIdentifier> WebAutomationSession::webFrameIDForHandle(const String& handle, bool& frameNotFound)
207{
208 if (handle.isEmpty())
209 return std::nullopt;
210
211 auto iter = m_handleWebFrameMap.find(handle);
212 if (iter == m_handleWebFrameMap.end()) {
213 frameNotFound = true;
214 return std::nullopt;
215 }
216
217 return iter->value;
218}
219
220String WebAutomationSession::handleForWebFrameID(std::optional<FrameIdentifier> frameID)
221{
222 if (!frameID || !*frameID)
223 return emptyString();
224
225 for (auto& process : m_processPool->processes()) {
226 if (WebFrameProxy* frame = process->webFrame(*frameID)) {
227 if (frame->isMainFrame())
228 return emptyString();
229 break;
230 }
231 }
232
233 auto iter = m_webFrameHandleMap.find(*frameID);
234 if (iter != m_webFrameHandleMap.end())
235 return iter->value;
236
237 String handle = "frame-" + createCanonicalUUIDString().convertToASCIIUppercase();
238
239 auto firstAddResult = m_webFrameHandleMap.add(*frameID, handle);
240 RELEASE_ASSERT(firstAddResult.isNewEntry);
241
242 auto secondAddResult = m_handleWebFrameMap.add(handle, *frameID);
243 RELEASE_ASSERT(secondAddResult.isNewEntry);
244
245 return handle;
246}
247
248String WebAutomationSession::handleForWebFrameProxy(const WebFrameProxy& webFrameProxy)
249{
250 return handleForWebFrameID(webFrameProxy.frameID());
251}
252
253Ref<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContext> WebAutomationSession::buildBrowsingContextForPage(WebPageProxy& page, WebCore::FloatRect windowFrame)
254{
255 auto originObject = Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Point::create()
256 .setX(windowFrame.x())
257 .setY(windowFrame.y())
258 .release();
259
260 auto sizeObject = Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Size::create()
261 .setWidth(windowFrame.width())
262 .setHeight(windowFrame.height())
263 .release();
264
265 bool isActive = page.isViewVisible() && page.isViewFocused() && page.isViewWindowActive();
266 String handle = handleForWebPageProxy(page);
267
268 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContext::create()
269 .setHandle(handle)
270 .setActive(isActive)
271 .setUrl(page.pageLoadState().activeURL())
272 .setWindowOrigin(WTFMove(originObject))
273 .setWindowSize(WTFMove(sizeObject))
274 .release();
275}

277// Platform-independent Commands.
278
279void WebAutomationSession::getNextContext(Ref<WebAutomationSession>&& protectedThis, Vector<Ref<WebPageProxy>>&& pages, Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContext>> contexts, Ref<WebAutomationSession::GetBrowsingContextsCallback>&& callback)
280{
281 if (pages.isEmpty()) {
282 callback->sendSuccess(WTFMove(contexts));
283 return;
284 }
285 auto page = pages.takeLast();
286 auto& webPageProxy = page.get();
287 webPageProxy.getWindowFrameWithCallback([this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), callback = WTFMove(callback), pages = WTFMove(pages), contexts = WTFMove(contexts), page = WTFMove(page)](WebCore::FloatRect windowFrame) mutable {
288 contexts->addItem(protectedThis->buildBrowsingContextForPage(page.get(), windowFrame));
289 getNextContext(WTFMove(protectedThis), WTFMove(pages), WTFMove(contexts), WTFMove(callback));
290 });
291}
292
293void WebAutomationSession::getBrowsingContexts(Ref<GetBrowsingContextsCallback>&& callback)
294{
295 Vector<Ref<WebPageProxy>> pages;
296 for (auto& process : m_processPool->processes()) {
297 for (auto* page : process->pages()) {
298 ASSERT(page);
299 if (!page->isControlledByAutomation())
300 continue;
301 pages.append(*page);
302 }
303 }
304
305 getNextContext(makeRef(*this), WTFMove(pages), JSON::ArrayOf<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContext>::create(), WTFMove(callback));
306}
307
308void WebAutomationSession::getBrowsingContext(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& handle, Ref<GetBrowsingContextCallback>&& callback)
309{
310 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(handle);
311 if (!page)
312 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
313
314 page->getWindowFrameWithCallback([protectedThis = makeRef(*this), page = makeRef(*page), callback = WTFMove(callback)](WebCore::FloatRect windowFrame) mutable {
315 callback->sendSuccess(protectedThis->buildBrowsingContextForPage(page.get(), windowFrame));
316 });
317}
318
319static Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextPresentation toProtocol(API::AutomationSessionClient::BrowsingContextPresentation value)
320{
321 switch (value) {
322 case API::AutomationSessionClient::BrowsingContextPresentation::Tab:
323 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextPresentation::Tab;
324 case API::AutomationSessionClient::BrowsingContextPresentation::Window:
325 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextPresentation::Window;
326 }
327
328 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
329}
330
331void WebAutomationSession::createBrowsingContext(std::optional<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextPresentation>&& presentationHint, Ref<CreateBrowsingContextCallback>&& callback)
332{
333 ASSERT(m_client);
334 if (!m_client)
335 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InternalError, "The remote session could not request a new browsing context.");
336
337 uint16_t options = 0;
338
339 if (presentationHint == Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextPresentation::Tab)
340 options |= API::AutomationSessionBrowsingContextOptionsPreferNewTab;
341
342 m_client->requestNewPageWithOptions(*this, static_cast<API::AutomationSessionBrowsingContextOptions>(options), [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback)](WebPageProxy* page) {
343 if (!page)
344 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InternalError, "The remote session failed to create a new browsing context.");
345
346 // WebDriver allows running commands in a browsing context which has not done any loads yet. Force WebProcess to be created so it can receive messages.
347 page->launchInitialProcessIfNecessary();
348 callback->sendSuccess(protectedThis->handleForWebPageProxy(*page), toProtocol(protectedThis->m_client->currentPresentationOfPage(protectedThis.get(), *page)));
349 });
350}
351
352Inspector::Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> WebAutomationSession::closeBrowsingContext(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& handle)
353{
354 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(handle);
355 if (!page)
356 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
357
358 page->closePage();
359
360 return { };
361}
362
363void WebAutomationSession::switchToBrowsingContext(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::FrameHandle& frameHandle, Ref<SwitchToBrowsingContextCallback>&& callback)
364{
365 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
366 if (!page)
367 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
368
369 bool frameNotFound = false;
370 webFrameIDForHandle(frameHandle, frameNotFound);
371 if (frameNotFound)
372 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(FrameNotFound);
373
374 // FIXME: Should we also switch to the frame that frameHandle points to?
375 m_client->requestSwitchToPage(*this, *page, [page = makeRef(*page), callback = WTFMove(callback)]() {
376 page->setFocus(true);
377
378 callback->sendSuccess();
379 });
380}
381
382void WebAutomationSession::setWindowFrameOfBrowsingContext(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& handle, RefPtr<JSON::Object>&& origin, RefPtr<JSON::Object>&& size, Ref<SetWindowFrameOfBrowsingContextCallback>&& callback)
383{
384 std::optional<double> x;
385 std::optional<double> y;
386 if (origin) {
387 x = origin->getDouble("x"_s);
388 if (!x)
389 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The 'x' parameter was not found or invalid.");
390
391 y = origin->getDouble("y"_s);
392 if (!y)
393 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The 'y' parameter was not found or invalid.");
394 }
395
396 std::optional<double> width;
397 std::optional<double> height;
398 if (size) {
399 width = size->getDouble("width"_s);
400 if (!width)
401 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The 'width' parameter was not found or invalid.");
402
403 height = size->getDouble("height"_s);
404 if (!height)
405 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The 'height' parameter was not found or invalid.");
406
407 if (width.value() < 0)
408 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The 'width' parameter had an invalid value.");
409
410 if (height.value() < 0)
411 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The 'height' parameter had an invalid value.");
412 }
413
414 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(handle);
415 if (!page)
416 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
417
418 exitFullscreenWindowForPage(*page, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback), page = makeRefPtr(page), width, height, x, y]() mutable {
419 auto& webPage = *page;
420 this->restoreWindowForPage(webPage, [callback = WTFMove(callback), page = WTFMove(page), width, height, x, y]() mutable {
421 auto& webPage = *page;
422 webPage.getWindowFrameWithCallback([callback = WTFMove(callback), page = WTFMove(page), width, height, x, y](WebCore::FloatRect originalFrame) mutable {
423 WebCore::FloatRect newFrame = WebCore::FloatRect(WebCore::FloatPoint(x.value_or(originalFrame.location().x()), y.value_or(originalFrame.location().y())), WebCore::FloatSize(width.value_or(originalFrame.size().width()), height.value_or(originalFrame.size().height())));
424 if (newFrame != originalFrame)
425 page->setWindowFrame(newFrame);
426
427 callback->sendSuccess();
428 });
429 });
430 });
431}
432
433void WebAutomationSession::waitForNavigationToComplete(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::FrameHandle& optionalFrameHandle, std::optional<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy>&& optionalPageLoadStrategy, std::optional<double>&& optionalPageLoadTimeout, Ref<WaitForNavigationToCompleteCallback>&& callback)
434{
435 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
436 if (!page)
437 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
438
439 auto pageLoadStrategy = optionalPageLoadStrategy.value_or(defaultPageLoadStrategy);
440 auto pageLoadTimeout = optionalPageLoadTimeout ? Seconds::fromMilliseconds(*optionalPageLoadTimeout) : defaultPageLoadTimeout;
441
442 // If page is loading and there's an active JavaScript dialog is probably because the
443 // dialog was started in an onload handler, so in case of normal page load strategy the
444 // load will not finish until the dialog is dismissed. Instead of waiting for the timeout,
445 // we return without waiting since we know it will timeout for sure. We want to check
446 // arguments first, though.
447 bool shouldTimeoutDueToUnexpectedAlert = pageLoadStrategy == Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::Normal
448 && page->pageLoadState().isLoading() && m_client->isShowingJavaScriptDialogOnPage(*this, *page);
449
450 if (!optionalFrameHandle.isEmpty()) {
451 bool frameNotFound = false;
452 auto frameID = webFrameIDForHandle(optionalFrameHandle, frameNotFound);
453 if (frameNotFound)
454 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(FrameNotFound);
455 WebFrameProxy* frame = page->process().webFrame(frameID.value());
456 if (!frame)
457 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(FrameNotFound);
458 if (!shouldTimeoutDueToUnexpectedAlert)
459 waitForNavigationToCompleteOnFrame(*frame, pageLoadStrategy, pageLoadTimeout, WTFMove(callback));
460 } else {
461 if (!shouldTimeoutDueToUnexpectedAlert)
462 waitForNavigationToCompleteOnPage(*page, pageLoadStrategy, pageLoadTimeout, WTFMove(callback));
463 }
464
465 if (shouldTimeoutDueToUnexpectedAlert) {
466 // ยง9 Navigation.
467 // 7. If the previous step completed by the session page load timeout being reached and the browser does not
468 // have an active user prompt, return error with error code timeout.
469 // 8. Return success with data null.
470 // https://w3c.github.io/webdriver/webdriver-spec.html#dfn-wait-for-navigation-to-complete
471 callback->sendSuccess();
472 }
473}
474
475void WebAutomationSession::waitForNavigationToCompleteOnPage(WebPageProxy& page, Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy loadStrategy, Seconds timeout, Ref<Inspector::BackendDispatcher::CallbackBase>&& callback)
476{
477 ASSERT(!m_loadTimer.isActive());
478 if (loadStrategy == Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::None || (!page.pageLoadState().isLoading() && !page.pageLoadState().hasUncommittedLoad())) {
479 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
480 return;
481 }
482
483 m_loadTimer.startOneShot(timeout);
484 switch (loadStrategy) {
485 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::Normal:
486 m_pendingNormalNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerPage.set(page.identifier(), WTFMove(callback));
487 break;
488 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::Eager:
489 m_pendingEagerNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerPage.set(page.identifier(), WTFMove(callback));
490 break;
491 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::None:
492 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
493 }
494}
495
496void WebAutomationSession::waitForNavigationToCompleteOnFrame(WebFrameProxy& frame, Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy loadStrategy, Seconds timeout, Ref<Inspector::BackendDispatcher::CallbackBase>&& callback)
497{
498 ASSERT(!m_loadTimer.isActive());
499 if (loadStrategy == Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::None || frame.frameLoadState().state() == FrameLoadState::State::Finished) {
500 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
501 return;
502 }
503
504 m_loadTimer.startOneShot(timeout);
505 switch (loadStrategy) {
506 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::Normal:
507 m_pendingNormalNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerFrame.set(frame.frameID(), WTFMove(callback));
508 break;
509 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::Eager:
510 m_pendingEagerNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerFrame.set(frame.frameID(), WTFMove(callback));
511 break;
512 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::PageLoadStrategy::None:
513 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
514 }
515}
516
517void WebAutomationSession::respondToPendingPageNavigationCallbacksWithTimeout(HashMap<WebPageProxyIdentifier, RefPtr<Inspector::BackendDispatcher::CallbackBase>>& map)
518{
519 auto timeoutError = STRING_FOR_PREDEFINED_ERROR_NAME(Timeout);
520 for (auto id : copyToVector(map.keys())) {
521 auto page = WebProcessProxy::webPage(id);
522 auto callback = map.take(id);
523 if (page && m_client->isShowingJavaScriptDialogOnPage(*this, *page))
524 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
525 else
526 callback->sendFailure(timeoutError);
527 }
528}
529
530static WebPageProxy* findPageForFrameID(const WebProcessPool& processPool, FrameIdentifier frameID)
531{
532 for (auto& process : processPool.processes()) {
533 if (auto* frame = process->webFrame(frameID))
534 return frame->page();
535 }
536 return nullptr;
537}
538
539void WebAutomationSession::respondToPendingFrameNavigationCallbacksWithTimeout(HashMap<FrameIdentifier, RefPtr<Inspector::BackendDispatcher::CallbackBase>>& map)
540{
541 auto timeoutError = STRING_FOR_PREDEFINED_ERROR_NAME(Timeout);
542 for (auto id : copyToVector(map.keys())) {
543 auto* page = findPageForFrameID(*m_processPool, id);
544 auto callback = map.take(id);
545 if (page && m_client->isShowingJavaScriptDialogOnPage(*this, *page))
546 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
547 else
548 callback->sendFailure(timeoutError);
549 }
550}
551
552void WebAutomationSession::loadTimerFired()
553{
554 respondToPendingFrameNavigationCallbacksWithTimeout(m_pendingNormalNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerFrame);
555 respondToPendingFrameNavigationCallbacksWithTimeout(m_pendingEagerNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerFrame);
556 respondToPendingPageNavigationCallbacksWithTimeout(m_pendingNormalNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerPage);
557 respondToPendingPageNavigationCallbacksWithTimeout(m_pendingEagerNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerPage);
558}
559
560void WebAutomationSession::maximizeWindowOfBrowsingContext(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, Ref<MaximizeWindowOfBrowsingContextCallback>&& callback)
561{
562 auto* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
563 if (!page)
564 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
565
566 exitFullscreenWindowForPage(*page, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback), page = makeRefPtr(page)]() mutable {
567 auto& webPage = *page;
568 restoreWindowForPage(webPage, [this, callback = WTFMove(callback), page = WTFMove(page)]() mutable {
569 maximizeWindowForPage(*page, [callback = WTFMove(callback)]() {
570 callback->sendSuccess();
571 });
572 });
573 });
574}
575
576void WebAutomationSession::hideWindowOfBrowsingContext(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, Ref<HideWindowOfBrowsingContextCallback>&& callback)
577{
578 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
579 if (!page)
580 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
581
582 exitFullscreenWindowForPage(*page, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback), page = makeRefPtr(page)]() mutable {
583 protectedThis->hideWindowForPage(*page, [callback = WTFMove(callback)]() mutable {
584 callback->sendSuccess();
585 });
586 });
587}
588
589void WebAutomationSession::exitFullscreenWindowForPage(WebPageProxy& page, WTF::CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
590{
591#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
592 ASSERT(!m_windowStateTransitionCallback);
593 if (!page.fullScreenManager() || !page.fullScreenManager()->isFullScreen()) {
594 completionHandler();
595 return;
596 }
597
598 m_windowStateTransitionCallback = WTF::Function<void(WindowTransitionedToState)> { [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](WindowTransitionedToState state) mutable {
599 // If fullscreen exited and we didn't request that, just ignore it.
600 if (state != WindowTransitionedToState::Unfullscreen)
601 return;
602
603 // Keep this callback in scope so completionHandler does not get destroyed before we call it.
604 auto protectedCallback = WTFMove(m_windowStateTransitionCallback);
605 completionHandler();
606 } };
607
608 page.fullScreenManager()->requestExitFullScreen();
609#else
610 completionHandler();
611#endif
612}

629void WebAutomationSession::willShowJavaScriptDialog(WebPageProxy& page)
630{
631 // Wait until the next run loop iteration to give time for the client to show the dialog,
632 // then check if the dialog is still present. If the page is loading, the dialog will block
633 // the load in case of normal strategy, so we want to dispatch all pending navigation callbacks.
634 // If the dialog was shown during a script execution, we want to finish the evaluateJavaScriptFunction
635 // operation with an unexpected alert open error.
636 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), page = makeRef(page)] {
637 if (!page->hasRunningProcess() || !m_client || !m_client->isShowingJavaScriptDialogOnPage(*this, page))
638 return;
639
640 if (page->pageLoadState().isLoading()) {
641 m_loadTimer.stop();
642 respondToPendingFrameNavigationCallbacksWithTimeout(m_pendingNormalNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerFrame);
643 respondToPendingPageNavigationCallbacksWithTimeout(m_pendingNormalNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerPage);
644 }
645
646 if (!m_evaluateJavaScriptFunctionCallbacks.isEmpty()) {
647 for (auto key : copyToVector(m_evaluateJavaScriptFunctionCallbacks.keys())) {
648 auto callback = m_evaluateJavaScriptFunctionCallbacks.take(key);
649 callback->sendSuccess("null"_s);
650 }
651 }
652
653#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
654 if (!m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.isEmpty()) {
655 for (auto key : copyToVector(m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.keys())) {
656 auto callback = m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(key);
657 callback(std::nullopt);
658 }
659 }
660#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
661
662#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
663 if (!m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.isEmpty()) {
664 for (auto key : copyToVector(m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.keys())) {
665 auto callback = m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(key);
666 callback(std::nullopt);
667 }
668 }
669#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
670 });
671
672#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_WHEEL_INTERACTIONS)
673 if (!m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.isEmpty()) {
674 for (auto key : copyToVector(m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.keys())) {
675 auto callback = m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(key);
676 callback(std::nullopt);
677 }
678 }
679#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_WHEEL_INTERACTIONS)
680}

746void WebAutomationSession::navigationOccurredForFrame(const WebFrameProxy& frame)
747{
748 if (frame.isMainFrame()) {
749 // New page loaded, clear frame handles previously cached for frame's page.
750 HashSet<String> handlesToRemove;
751 for (const auto& iter : m_handleWebFrameMap) {
752 auto* webFrame = frame.page()->process().webFrame(iter.value);
753 if (webFrame && webFrame->page() == frame.page()) {
754 handlesToRemove.add(iter.key);
755 m_webFrameHandleMap.remove(iter.value);
756 }
757 }
758 m_handleWebFrameMap.removeIf([&](auto& iter) {
759 return handlesToRemove.contains(iter.key);
760 });
761
762 if (auto callback = m_pendingNormalNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerPage.take(frame.page()->identifier())) {
763 m_loadTimer.stop();
764 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
765 }
766 m_domainNotifier->browsingContextCleared(handleForWebPageProxy(*frame.page()));
767 } else {
768 if (auto callback = m_pendingNormalNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerFrame.take(frame.frameID())) {
769 m_loadTimer.stop();
770 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
771 }
772 }
773}
774
775void WebAutomationSession::documentLoadedForFrame(const WebFrameProxy& frame)
776{
777 if (frame.isMainFrame()) {
778 if (auto callback = m_pendingEagerNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerPage.take(frame.page()->identifier())) {
779 m_loadTimer.stop();
780 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
781 }
782
783#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
784 resetClickCount();
785#endif
786 } else {
787 if (auto callback = m_pendingEagerNavigationInBrowsingContextCallbacksPerFrame.take(frame.frameID())) {
788 m_loadTimer.stop();
789 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
790 }
791 }
792}

795{
796 if (auto callback = m_pendingInspectorCallbacksPerPage.take(page.identifier()))
797 callback->sendSuccess(JSON::Object::create());
798}

830void WebAutomationSession::willClosePage(const WebPageProxy& page)
831{
832 String handle = handleForWebPageProxy(page);
833 m_domainNotifier->browsingContextCleared(handle);
834
835 // Cancel pending interactions on this page. By providing an error, this will cause subsequent
836 // actions to be aborted and the SimulatedInputDispatcher::run() call will unwind and fail.
837#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
838 if (auto callback = m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(page.identifier()))
839 callback(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(WindowNotFound));
840#endif
841#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
842 if (auto callback = m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(page.identifier()))
843 callback(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(WindowNotFound));
844#endif
845#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_WHEEL_INTERACTIONS)
846 if (auto callback = m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(page.identifier()))
847 callback(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(WindowNotFound));
848#endif
849
850#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_ACTIONS_API)
851 // Then tell the input dispatcher to cancel so timers are stopped, and let it go out of scope.
852 if (auto inputDispatcher = m_inputDispatchersByPage.take(page.identifier()))
853 inputDispatcher->cancel();
854#endif
855}
856
857static bool fileCanBeAcceptedForUpload(const String& filename, const HashSet<String>& allowedMIMETypes, const HashSet<String>& allowedFileExtensions)
858{
859 if (!FileSystem::fileExists(filename))
860 return false;
861
862 if (allowedMIMETypes.isEmpty() && allowedFileExtensions.isEmpty())
863 return true;
864
865 // We can't infer a MIME type from a file without an extension, just give up.
866 auto dotOffset = filename.reverseFind('.');
867 if (dotOffset == notFound)
868 return false;
869
870 String extension = filename.substring(dotOffset + 1).convertToASCIILowercase();
871 if (extension.isEmpty())
872 return false;
873
874 if (allowedFileExtensions.contains(extension))
875 return true;
876
877 String mappedMIMEType = WebCore::MIMETypeRegistry::mimeTypeForExtension(extension).convertToASCIILowercase();
878 if (mappedMIMEType.isEmpty())
879 return false;
880
881 if (allowedMIMETypes.contains(mappedMIMEType))
882 return true;
883
884 // Fall back to checking for a MIME type wildcard if an exact match is not found.
885 Vector<String> components = mappedMIMEType.split('/');
886 if (components.size() != 2)
887 return false;
888
889 auto wildcardedMIMEType = makeString(components[0], "/*");
890 if (allowedMIMETypes.contains(wildcardedMIMEType))
891 return true;
892
893 return false;
894}
895
896void WebAutomationSession::handleRunOpenPanel(const WebPageProxy& page, const WebFrameProxy&, const API::OpenPanelParameters& parameters, WebOpenPanelResultListenerProxy& resultListener)
897{
898 String browsingContextHandle = handleForWebPageProxy(page);
899 if (!m_filesToSelectForFileUpload.size()) {
900 resultListener.cancel();
901 m_domainNotifier->fileChooserDismissed(browsingContextHandle, true, { });
902 return;
903 }
904
905 if (m_filesToSelectForFileUpload.size() > 1 && !parameters.allowMultipleFiles()) {
906 resultListener.cancel();
907 m_domainNotifier->fileChooserDismissed(browsingContextHandle, true, { });
908 return;
909 }
910
911 HashSet<String> allowedMIMETypes;
912 auto acceptMIMETypes = parameters.acceptMIMETypes();
913 for (auto type : acceptMIMETypes->elementsOfType<API::String>())
914 allowedMIMETypes.add(type->string());
915
916 HashSet<String> allowedFileExtensions;
917 auto acceptFileExtensions = parameters.acceptFileExtensions();
918 for (auto type : acceptFileExtensions->elementsOfType<API::String>()) {
919 // WebCore vends extensions with leading periods. Strip these to simplify matching later.
920 String extension = type->string();
921 ASSERT(extension.characterAt(0) == '.');
922 allowedFileExtensions.add(extension.substring(1));
923 }
924
925 // Per ยง14.3.10.5 in the W3C spec, if at least one file cannot be accepted, the command should fail.
926 for (const String& filename : m_filesToSelectForFileUpload) {
927 if (!fileCanBeAcceptedForUpload(filename, allowedMIMETypes, allowedFileExtensions)) {
928 resultListener.cancel();
929 m_domainNotifier->fileChooserDismissed(browsingContextHandle, true, { });
930 return;
931 }
932 }
933
934 // Copy the file list we used before calling out to the open panel listener.
935 Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<String>> selectedFiles = JSON::ArrayOf<String>::create();
936 for (const String& filename : m_filesToSelectForFileUpload)
937 selectedFiles->addItem(filename);
938
939 resultListener.chooseFiles(m_filesToSelectForFileUpload);
940
941 m_domainNotifier->fileChooserDismissed(browsingContextHandle, false, WTFMove(selectedFiles));
942}

944void WebAutomationSession::evaluateJavaScriptFunction(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::FrameHandle& frameHandle, const String& function, Ref<JSON::Array>&& arguments, std::optional<bool>&& expectsImplicitCallbackArgument, std::optional<double>&& callbackTimeout, Ref<EvaluateJavaScriptFunctionCallback>&& callback)
945{
946 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
947 if (!page)
948 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
949
950 bool frameNotFound = false;
951 auto frameID = webFrameIDForHandle(frameHandle, frameNotFound);
952 if (frameNotFound)
953 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(FrameNotFound);
954
955 Vector<String> argumentsVector;
956 argumentsVector.reserveCapacity(arguments->length());
957
958 for (const auto& argument : arguments.get())
959 argumentsVector.uncheckedAppend(argument->asString());
960
961 uint64_t callbackID = m_nextEvaluateJavaScriptCallbackID++;
962 m_evaluateJavaScriptFunctionCallbacks.set(callbackID, WTFMove(callback));
963
964 page->process().send(Messages::WebAutomationSessionProxy::EvaluateJavaScriptFunction(page->webPageID(), frameID, function, argumentsVector, expectsImplicitCallbackArgument.value_or(false), WTFMove(callbackTimeout), callbackID), 0);
965}
966
967void WebAutomationSession::didEvaluateJavaScriptFunction(uint64_t callbackID, const String& result, const String& errorType)
968{
969 auto callback = m_evaluateJavaScriptFunctionCallbacks.take(callbackID);
970 if (!callback)
971 return;
972
973 if (!errorType.isEmpty())
974 callback->sendFailure(STRING_FOR_PREDEFINED_ERROR_MESSAGE_AND_DETAILS(errorType, result));
975 else
976 callback->sendSuccess(result);
977}

979void WebAutomationSession::resolveChildFrameHandle(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::FrameHandle& frameHandle, std::optional<int>&& optionalOrdinal, const String& optionalName, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::NodeHandle& optionalNodeHandle, Ref<ResolveChildFrameHandleCallback>&& callback)
980{
981 if (!optionalOrdinal && !optionalName && !optionalNodeHandle)
982 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "Command must specify a child frame by ordinal, name, or element handle.");
983
984 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
985 if (!page)
986 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
987
988 bool frameNotFound = false;
989 auto frameID = webFrameIDForHandle(frameHandle, frameNotFound);
990 if (frameNotFound)
991 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(FrameNotFound);
992
993 WTF::CompletionHandler<void(std::optional<String>, std::optional<FrameIdentifier>)> completionHandler = [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), callback](std::optional<String> errorType, std::optional<FrameIdentifier> frameID) mutable {
994 if (errorType) {
995 callback->sendFailure(STRING_FOR_PREDEFINED_ERROR_MESSAGE(*errorType));
996 return;
997 }
998
999 callback->sendSuccess(handleForWebFrameID(frameID));
1000 };
1001
1002 if (!!optionalNodeHandle) {
1003 page->process().sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::WebAutomationSessionProxy::ResolveChildFrameWithNodeHandle(page->webPageID(), frameID, optionalNodeHandle), WTFMove(completionHandler));
1004 return;
1005 }
1006
1007 if (!!optionalName) {
1008 page->process().sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::WebAutomationSessionProxy::ResolveChildFrameWithName(page->webPageID(), frameID, optionalName), WTFMove(completionHandler));
1009 return;
1010 }
1011
1012 if (optionalOrdinal) {
1013 page->process().sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::WebAutomationSessionProxy::ResolveChildFrameWithOrdinal(page->webPageID(), frameID, *optionalOrdinal), WTFMove(completionHandler));
1014 return;
1015 }
1016
1017 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1018}

1043static std::optional<CoordinateSystem> protocolStringToCoordinateSystem(Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CoordinateSystem coordinateSystem)
1044{
1045 switch (coordinateSystem) {
1046 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CoordinateSystem::Page:
1047 return CoordinateSystem::Page;
1048
1049 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CoordinateSystem::Viewport:
1050 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CoordinateSystem::LayoutViewport:
1051 return CoordinateSystem::LayoutViewport;
1052 }
1053
1054 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1055 return std::nullopt;
1056}

1058void WebAutomationSession::computeElementLayout(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::FrameHandle& frameHandle, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::NodeHandle& nodeHandle, std::optional<bool>&& optionalScrollIntoViewIfNeeded, Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CoordinateSystem coordinateSystemValue, Ref<ComputeElementLayoutCallback>&& callback)
1059{
1060 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
1061 if (!page)
1062 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
1063
1064 bool frameNotFound = false;
1065 auto frameID = webFrameIDForHandle(frameHandle, frameNotFound);
1066 if (frameNotFound)
1067 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(FrameNotFound);
1068
1069 std::optional<CoordinateSystem> coordinateSystem = protocolStringToCoordinateSystem(coordinateSystemValue);
1070 if (!coordinateSystem)
1071 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The parameter 'coordinateSystem' is invalid.");
1072
1073 WTF::CompletionHandler<void(std::optional<String>, WebCore::IntRect, std::optional<WebCore::IntPoint>, bool)> completionHandler = [callback](std::optional<String> errorType, WebCore::IntRect rect, std::optional<WebCore::IntPoint> inViewCenterPoint, bool isObscured) mutable {
1074 if (errorType) {
1075 callback->sendFailure(STRING_FOR_PREDEFINED_ERROR_MESSAGE(*errorType));
1076 return;
1077 }
1078
1079 auto originObject = Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Point::create()
1080 .setX(rect.x())
1081 .setY(rect.y())
1082 .release();
1083
1084 auto sizeObject = Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Size::create()
1085 .setWidth(rect.width())
1086 .setHeight(rect.height())
1087 .release();
1088
1089 auto rectObject = Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Rect::create()
1090 .setOrigin(WTFMove(originObject))
1091 .setSize(WTFMove(sizeObject))
1092 .release();
1093
1094 if (!inViewCenterPoint) {
1095 callback->sendSuccess(WTFMove(rectObject), nullptr, isObscured);
1096 return;
1097 }
1098
1099 auto inViewCenterPointObject = Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Point::create()
1100 .setX(inViewCenterPoint.value().x())
1101 .setY(inViewCenterPoint.value().y())
1102 .release();
1103
1104 callback->sendSuccess(WTFMove(rectObject), WTFMove(inViewCenterPointObject), isObscured);
1105 };
1106
1107 bool scrollIntoViewIfNeeded = optionalScrollIntoViewIfNeeded ? *optionalScrollIntoViewIfNeeded : false;
1108 page->process().sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::WebAutomationSessionProxy::ComputeElementLayout(page->webPageID(), frameID, nodeHandle, scrollIntoViewIfNeeded, coordinateSystem.value()), WTFMove(completionHandler));
1109}

1147Inspector::Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> WebAutomationSession::dismissCurrentJavaScriptDialog(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle)
1148{
1149 ASSERT(m_client);
1150 if (!m_client)
1151 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(InternalError);

1161
1162 return { };
1163}

1165Inspector::Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> WebAutomationSession::acceptCurrentJavaScriptDialog(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle)

1198
1199Inspector::Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> WebAutomationSession::setUserInputForCurrentJavaScriptPrompt(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, const String& promptValue)
1200{
1201 ASSERT(m_client);
1202 if (!m_client)
1203 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(InternalError);
1204
1205 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
1206 if (!page)
1207 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
1208
1209 if (!m_client->isShowingJavaScriptDialogOnPage(*this, *page))
1210 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(NoJavaScriptDialog);
1211
1212 // ยง18.4 Send Alert Text.
1213 // https://w3c.github.io/webdriver/webdriver-spec.html#send-alert-text
1214 // 3. Run the substeps of the first matching current user prompt:
1215 auto scriptDialogType = m_client->typeOfCurrentJavaScriptDialogOnPage(*this, *page);
1216 ASSERT(scriptDialogType);
1217 switch (scriptDialogType.value()) {
1218 case API::AutomationSessionClient::JavaScriptDialogType::Alert:
1219 case API::AutomationSessionClient::JavaScriptDialogType::Confirm:
1220 // Return error with error code element not interactable.
1221 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(ElementNotInteractable);
1222 case API::AutomationSessionClient::JavaScriptDialogType::Prompt:
1223 // Do nothing.
1224 break;
1225 case API::AutomationSessionClient::JavaScriptDialogType::BeforeUnloadConfirm:
1226 // Return error with error code unsupported operation.
1227 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(NotImplemented);
1228 }
1229
1230 m_client->setUserInputForCurrentJavaScriptPromptOnPage(*this, *page, promptValue);
1231
1232 return { };
1233}
1234
1235Inspector::Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> WebAutomationSession::setFilesToSelectForFileUpload(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, Ref<JSON::Array>&& filenames, RefPtr<JSON::Array>&& fileContents)
1236{
1237 Vector<String> newFileList;
1238 newFileList.reserveInitialCapacity(filenames->length());
1239
1240 if (fileContents && fileContents->length() != filenames->length())
1241 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InternalError, "The parameters 'filenames' and 'fileContents' must have equal length.");
1242
1243 for (size_t i = 0; i < filenames->length(); ++i) {
1244 auto filename = filenames->get(i)->asString();
1245 if (!filename)
1246 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InternalError, "The parameter 'filenames' contains a non-string value.");
1247
1248 if (!fileContents) {
1249 newFileList.append(filename);
1250 continue;
1251 }
1252
1253 auto fileData = fileContents->get(i)->asString();
1254 if (!fileData)
1255 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InternalError, "The parameter 'fileContents' contains a non-string value.");
1256
1257 std::optional<String> localFilePath = platformGenerateLocalFilePathForRemoteFile(filename, fileData);
1258 if (!localFilePath)
1259 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InternalError, "The remote file could not be saved to a local temporary directory.");
1260
1261 newFileList.append(localFilePath.value());
1262 }
1263
1264 m_filesToSelectForFileUpload.swap(newFileList);
1265
1266 return { };
1267}

1269void WebAutomationSession::setFilesForInputFileUpload(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::FrameHandle& frameHandle, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::NodeHandle& nodeHandle, Ref<JSON::Array>&& filenames, Ref<SetFilesForInputFileUploadCallback>&& callback)
1270{
1271 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
1272 if (!page)
1273 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
1274
1275 bool frameNotFound = false;
1276 auto frameID = webFrameIDForHandle(frameHandle, frameNotFound);
1277 if (frameNotFound)
1278 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(FrameNotFound);
1279
1280 Vector<String> newFileList;
1281 newFileList.reserveInitialCapacity(filenames->length());
1282 for (size_t i = 0; i < filenames->length(); ++i) {
1283 auto filename = filenames->get(i)->asString();
1284 if (!filename)
1285 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InternalError, "The parameter 'filenames' contains a non-string value.");
1286
1287 newFileList.append(filename);
1288 }
1289
1290 CompletionHandler<void(std::optional<String>)> completionHandler = [callback](std::optional<String> errorType) mutable {
1291 if (errorType) {
1292 callback->sendFailure(STRING_FOR_PREDEFINED_ERROR_MESSAGE(*errorType));
1293 return;
1294 }
1295
1296 callback->sendSuccess();
1297 };
1298
1299 page->process().sendWithAsyncReply(Messages::WebAutomationSessionProxy::SetFilesForInputFileUpload(page->webPageID(), frameID, nodeHandle, WTFMove(newFileList)), WTFMove(completionHandler));
1300}
1301
1302static inline Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy toProtocolSameSitePolicy(WebCore::Cookie::SameSitePolicy policy)
1303{
1304 switch (policy) {
1305 case WebCore::Cookie::SameSitePolicy::None:
1306 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy::None;
1307 case WebCore::Cookie::SameSitePolicy::Lax:
1308 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy::Lax;
1309 case WebCore::Cookie::SameSitePolicy::Strict:
1310 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy::Strict;
1311 }
1312 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1313}
1314
1315static inline WebCore::Cookie::SameSitePolicy toWebCoreSameSitePolicy(Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy policy)
1316{
1317 switch (policy) {
1318 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy::None:
1319 return WebCore::Cookie::SameSitePolicy::None;
1320 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy::Lax:
1321 return WebCore::Cookie::SameSitePolicy::Lax;
1322 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy::Strict:
1323 return WebCore::Cookie::SameSitePolicy::Strict;
1324 }
1325 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1326}
1327
1328static Ref<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Cookie> buildObjectForCookie(const WebCore::Cookie& cookie)
1329{
1330 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Cookie::create()
1331 .setName(cookie.name)
1332 .setValue(cookie.value)
1333 .setDomain(cookie.domain)
1334 .setPath(cookie.path)
1335 .setExpires(cookie.expires ? *cookie.expires / 1000 : 0)
1336 .setSize((cookie.name.length() + cookie.value.length()))
1337 .setHttpOnly(cookie.httpOnly)
1338 .setSecure(cookie.secure)
1339 .setSession(cookie.session)
1340 .setSameSite(toProtocolSameSitePolicy(cookie.sameSite))
1341 .release();
1342}
1343
1344static Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Cookie>> buildArrayForCookies(Vector<WebCore::Cookie>& cookiesList)
1345{
1346 auto cookies = JSON::ArrayOf<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Cookie>::create();
1347
1348 for (const auto& cookie : cookiesList)
1349 cookies->addItem(buildObjectForCookie(cookie));
1350
1351 return cookies;
1352}

1357 if (!page)

1389
1390static String domainByAddingDotPrefixIfNeeded(String domain)
1391{
1392 if (domain[0] != '.') {
1393 // RFC 2965: If an explicitly specified value does not start with a dot, the user agent supplies a leading dot.
1394 // Assume that any host that ends with a digit is trying to be an IP address.
1395 if (!URL::hostIsIPAddress(domain))
1396 return makeString('.', domain);
1397 }
1398
1399 return domain;
1400}
1401
1402void WebAutomationSession::addSingleCookie(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle, Ref<JSON::Object>&& cookieObject, Ref<AddSingleCookieCallback>&& callback)
1403{
1404 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
1405 if (!page)
1406 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
1407
1408 URL activeURL = URL(URL(), page->pageLoadState().activeURL());
1409 ASSERT(activeURL.isValid());
1410
1411 WebCore::Cookie cookie;
1412
1413 cookie.name = cookieObject->getString("name"_s);
1414 if (!cookie.name)
1415 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'name' was not found.");
1416
1417 cookie.value = cookieObject->getString("value"_s);
1418 if (!cookie.value)
1419 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'value' was not found.");
1420
1421 auto domain = cookieObject->getString("domain"_s);
1422 if (!domain)
1423 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'domain' was not found.");
1424
1425 // Inherit the domain/host from the main frame's URL if it is not explicitly set.
1426 if (domain.isEmpty())
1427 cookie.domain = activeURL.host().toString();
1428 else
1429 cookie.domain = domainByAddingDotPrefixIfNeeded(domain);
1430
1431 cookie.path = cookieObject->getString("path"_s);
1432 if (!cookie.path)
1433 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'path' was not found.");
1434
1435 auto expires = cookieObject->getDouble("expires"_s);
1436 if (!expires)
1437 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'expires' was not found.");
1438
1439 cookie.expires = *expires * 1000.0;
1440
1441 auto secure = cookieObject->getBoolean("secure"_s);
1442 if (!secure)
1443 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'secure' was not found.");
1444
1445 cookie.secure = *secure;
1446
1447 auto session = cookieObject->getBoolean("session"_s);
1448 if (!session)
1449 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'session' was not found.");
1450
1451 cookie.session = *session;
1452
1453 auto httpOnly = cookieObject->getBoolean("httpOnly"_s);
1454 if (!httpOnly)
1455 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'httpOnly' was not found.");
1456
1457 cookie.httpOnly = *httpOnly;
1458
1459 auto sameSite = cookieObject->getString("sameSite"_s);
1460 if (!sameSite)
1461 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'sameSite' was not found.");
1462
1463 auto parsedSameSite = Inspector::Protocol::AutomationHelpers::parseEnumValueFromString<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::CookieSameSitePolicy>(sameSite);
1464 if (!parsedSameSite)
1465 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The parameter 'sameSite' has an unknown value.");
1466
1467 cookie.sameSite = toWebCoreSameSitePolicy(*parsedSameSite);
1468
1469 WebCookieManagerProxy& cookieManager = page->websiteDataStore().networkProcess().cookieManager();
1470 cookieManager.setCookies(page->websiteDataStore().sessionID(), { cookie }, [callback]() {
1471 callback->sendSuccess();
1472 });
1473}
1474
1475Inspector::Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> WebAutomationSession::deleteAllCookies(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& browsingContextHandle)
1476{
1477 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(browsingContextHandle);
1478 if (!page)
1479 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
1480
1481 URL activeURL = URL(URL(), page->pageLoadState().activeURL());
1482 ASSERT(activeURL.isValid());
1483
1484 String host = activeURL.host().toString();
1485
1486 WebCookieManagerProxy& cookieManager = page->websiteDataStore().networkProcess().cookieManager();
1487 cookieManager.deleteCookiesForHostnames(page->websiteDataStore().sessionID(), { host, domainByAddingDotPrefixIfNeeded(host) });
1488
1489 return { };
1490}

1492Inspector::Protocol::ErrorStringOr<Ref<JSON::ArrayOf<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::SessionPermissionData>>> WebAutomationSession::getSessionPermissions()
1493{
1494 auto permissionsObjectArray = JSON::ArrayOf<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::SessionPermissionData>::create();
1495 auto getUserMediaPermissionObject = Inspector::Protocol::Automation::SessionPermissionData::create()
1496 .setPermission(Inspector::Protocol::Automation::SessionPermission::GetUserMedia)
1497 .setValue(m_permissionForGetUserMedia)
1498 .release();
1499
1500 permissionsObjectArray->addItem(WTFMove(getUserMediaPermissionObject));
1501 return permissionsObjectArray;
1502}
1503
1504Inspector::Protocol::ErrorStringOr<void> WebAutomationSession::setSessionPermissions(Ref<JSON::Array>&& permissions)
1505{
1506 for (auto it = permissions->begin(); it != permissions->end(); ++it) {
1507 auto permission = it->get().asObject();
1508 if (!permission)
1509 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The parameter 'permissions' is invalid.");
1510
1511 auto permissionName = permission->getString("permission"_s);
1512 if (!permissionName)
1513 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The parameter 'permission' is missing or invalid.");
1514
1515 auto parsedPermissionName = Inspector::Protocol::AutomationHelpers::parseEnumValueFromString<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::SessionPermission>(permissionName);
1516 if (!parsedPermissionName)
1517 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The parameter 'permission' has an unknown value.");
1518
1519 auto permissionValue = permission->getBoolean("value"_s);
1520 if (!permissionValue)
1521 SYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The parameter 'value' is missing or invalid.");
1522
1523 switch (parsedPermissionName.value()) {
1524 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::SessionPermission::GetUserMedia:
1525 m_permissionForGetUserMedia = *permissionValue;
1526 break;
1527 }
1528 }
1529
1530 return { };
1531}
1532
1533bool WebAutomationSession::shouldAllowGetUserMediaForPage(const WebPageProxy&) const
1534{
1535 return m_permissionForGetUserMedia;
1536}

1538bool WebAutomationSession::isSimulatingUserInteraction() const
1539{
1540#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
1541 if (!m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.isEmpty())
1542 return true;
1543#endif
1544#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
1545 if (!m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.isEmpty())
1546 return true;
1547#endif
1548#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_WHEEL_INTERACTIONS)
1549 if (!m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.isEmpty())
1550 return true;
1551#endif
1552#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_TOUCH_INTERACTIONS)
1553 if (m_simulatingTouchInteraction)
1554 return true;
1555#endif
1556 return false;
1557}

1568void WebAutomationSession::viewportInViewCenterPointOfElement(WebPageProxy& page, std::optional<FrameIdentifier> frameID, const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::NodeHandle& nodeHandle, Function<void(std::optional<WebCore::IntPoint>, std::optional<AutomationCommandError>)>&& completionHandler)
1569{
1570 WTF::CompletionHandler<void(std::optional<String>, WebCore::IntRect, std::optional<WebCore::IntPoint>, bool)> didComputeElementLayoutHandler = [completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](std::optional<String> errorType, WebCore::IntRect, std::optional<WebCore::IntPoint> inViewCenterPoint, bool) mutable {

1582 };

1587#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
1588void WebAutomationSession::updateClickCount(MouseButton button, const WebCore::IntPoint& position, Seconds maxTime, int maxDistance)
1589{
1590 auto now = MonotonicTime::now();
1591 if (now - m_lastClickTime < maxTime && button == m_lastClickButton && m_lastClickPosition.distanceSquaredToPoint(position) < maxDistance) {
1592 m_clickCount++;
1593 m_lastClickTime = now;
1594 return;
1595 }
1596
1597 m_clickCount = 1;
1598 m_lastClickTime = now;
1599 m_lastClickButton = button;
1600 m_lastClickPosition = position;
1601}
1602
1603void WebAutomationSession::resetClickCount()
1604{
1605 m_clickCount = 1;
1606 m_lastClickButton = MouseButton::None;
1607 m_lastClickPosition = { };
1608}

1610void WebAutomationSession::simulateMouseInteraction(WebPageProxy& page, MouseInteraction interaction, MouseButton mouseButton, const WebCore::IntPoint& locationInViewport, const String& pointerType, CompletionHandler<void(std::optional<AutomationCommandError>)>&& completionHandler)
1611{
1612 page.getWindowFrameWithCallback([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), page = makeRef(page), interaction, mouseButton, locationInViewport, pointerType](WebCore::FloatRect windowFrame) mutable {
1613 auto clippedX = std::min(std::max(0.0f, (float)locationInViewport.x()), windowFrame.size().width());
1614 auto clippedY = std::min(std::max(0.0f, (float)locationInViewport.y()), windowFrame.size().height());
1615 if (clippedX != locationInViewport.x() || clippedY != locationInViewport.y()) {
1616 completionHandler(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(TargetOutOfBounds));
1617 return;
1618 }
1619
1620 // Bridge the flushed callback to our command's completion handler.
1621 auto mouseEventsFlushedCallback = [completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](std::optional<AutomationCommandError> error) mutable {
1622 completionHandler(error);
1623 };
1624
1625 auto& callbackInMap = m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.add(page->identifier(), nullptr).iterator->value;
1626 if (callbackInMap)
1627 callbackInMap(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(Timeout));
1628 callbackInMap = WTFMove(mouseEventsFlushedCallback);
1629
1630 platformSimulateMouseInteraction(page, interaction, mouseButton, locationInViewport, platformWebModifiersFromRaw(m_currentModifiers), pointerType);
1631
1632 // If the event does not hit test anything in the window, then it may not have been delivered.
1633 if (callbackInMap && !page->isProcessingMouseEvents()) {
1634 auto callbackToCancel = m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(page->identifier());
1635 callbackToCancel(std::nullopt);
1636 }
1637
1638 // Otherwise, wait for mouseEventsFlushedCallback to run when all events are handled.
1639 });
1640}
1641#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
1642
1643#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_TOUCH_INTERACTIONS)
1644void WebAutomationSession::simulateTouchInteraction(WebPageProxy& page, TouchInteraction interaction, const WebCore::IntPoint& locationInViewport, std::optional<Seconds> duration, CompletionHandler<void(std::optional<AutomationCommandError>)>&& completionHandler)
1645{
1646#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1647 WebCore::FloatRect visualViewportBounds = WebCore::FloatRect({ }, page.unobscuredContentRect().size());
1648 if (!visualViewportBounds.contains(locationInViewport)) {
1649 completionHandler(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(TargetOutOfBounds));
1650 return;
1651 }
1652#endif
1653
1654 m_simulatingTouchInteraction = true;
1655 platformSimulateTouchInteraction(page, interaction, locationInViewport, duration, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](std::optional<AutomationCommandError> error) mutable {
1656 m_simulatingTouchInteraction = false;
1657 completionHandler(error);
1658 });
1659}
1660#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_TOUCH_INTERACTIONS)
1661
1662#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
1663void WebAutomationSession::simulateKeyboardInteraction(WebPageProxy& page, KeyboardInteraction interaction, WTF::Variant<VirtualKey, CharKey>&& key, CompletionHandler<void(std::optional<AutomationCommandError>)>&& completionHandler)
1664{
1665 // Bridge the flushed callback to our command's completion handler.
1666 auto keyboardEventsFlushedCallback = [completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](std::optional<AutomationCommandError> error) mutable {
1667 completionHandler(error);
1668 };
1669
1670 auto& callbackInMap = m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.add(page.identifier(), nullptr).iterator->value;
1671 if (callbackInMap)
1672 callbackInMap(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(Timeout));
1673 callbackInMap = WTFMove(keyboardEventsFlushedCallback);
1674
1675 platformSimulateKeyboardInteraction(page, interaction, WTFMove(key));
1676
1677 // If the interaction does not generate any events, then do not wait for events to be flushed.
1678 // This happens in some corner cases on macOS, such as releasing a key while Command is pressed.
1679 if (callbackInMap && !page.isProcessingKeyboardEvents()) {
1680 auto callbackToCancel = m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(page.identifier());
1681 callbackToCancel(std::nullopt);
1682 }
1683
1684 // Otherwise, wait for keyboardEventsFlushedCallback to run when all events are handled.
1685}
1686#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
1687
1688#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_WHEEL_INTERACTIONS)
1689void WebAutomationSession::simulateWheelInteraction(WebPageProxy& page, const WebCore::IntPoint& locationInViewport, const WebCore::IntSize& delta, AutomationCompletionHandler&& completionHandler)
1690{
1691 page.getWindowFrameWithCallback([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), page = makeRef(page), locationInViewport, delta](WebCore::FloatRect windowFrame) mutable {
1692 auto clippedX = std::min(std::max(0.0f, static_cast<float>(locationInViewport.x())), windowFrame.size().width());
1693 auto clippedY = std::min(std::max(0.0f, static_cast<float>(locationInViewport.y())), windowFrame.size().height());
1694 if (clippedX != locationInViewport.x() || clippedY != locationInViewport.y()) {
1695 completionHandler(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(TargetOutOfBounds));
1696 return;
1697 }
1698
1699 // Bridge the flushed callback to our command's completion handler.
1700 auto wheelEventsFlushedCallback = [completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](std::optional<AutomationCommandError> error) mutable {
1701 completionHandler(error);
1702 };
1703
1704 auto& callbackInMap = m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.add(page->identifier(), nullptr).iterator->value;
1705 if (callbackInMap)
1706 callbackInMap(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(Timeout));
1707 callbackInMap = WTFMove(wheelEventsFlushedCallback);
1708
1709 platformSimulateWheelInteraction(page, locationInViewport, delta);
1710
1711 // If the event does not hit test anything in the window, then it may not have been delivered.
1712 if (callbackInMap && !page->isProcessingWheelEvents()) {
1713 auto callbackToCancel = m_pendingWheelEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(page->identifier());
1714 callbackToCancel(std::nullopt);
1715 }
1716
1717 // Otherwise, wait for wheelEventsFlushedCallback to run when all events are handled.
1718 });
1719}
1720#endif
1721#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_ACTIONS_API)
1722
1723#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
1724static WebEvent::Modifier protocolModifierToWebEventModifier(Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyModifier modifier)
1725{
1726 switch (modifier) {
1727 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyModifier::Alt:
1728 return WebEvent::Modifier::AltKey;
1729 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyModifier::Meta:
1730 return WebEvent::Modifier::MetaKey;
1731 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyModifier::Control:
1732 return WebEvent::Modifier::ControlKey;
1733 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyModifier::Shift:
1734 return WebEvent::Modifier::ShiftKey;
1735 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyModifier::CapsLock:
1736 return WebEvent::Modifier::CapsLockKey;
1737 }
1738
1739 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1740}
1741#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
1742
1743void WebAutomationSession::performMouseInteraction(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& handle, Ref<JSON::Object>&& requestedPosition, Inspector::Protocol::Automation::MouseButton mouseButton, Inspector::Protocol::Automation::MouseInteraction mouseInteraction, Ref<JSON::Array>&& keyModifierStrings, Ref<PerformMouseInteractionCallback>&& callback)
1744{
1745#if !ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
1746 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(NotImplemented);
1747#else
1748 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(handle);
1749 if (!page)
1750 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
1751
1752 auto x = requestedPosition->getDouble("x"_s);
1753 if (!x)
1754 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'x' was not found.");
1755
1756 auto floatX = static_cast<float>(*x);
1757
1758 auto y = requestedPosition->getDouble("y"_s);
1759 if (!y)
1760 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "The parameter 'y' was not found.");
1761
1762 auto floatY = static_cast<float>(*y);
1763
1764 OptionSet<WebEvent::Modifier> keyModifiers;
1765 for (auto it = keyModifierStrings->begin(); it != keyModifierStrings->end(); ++it) {
1766 auto modifierString = it->get().asString();
1767 if (!modifierString)
1768 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The parameter 'modifiers' is invalid.");
1769
1770 auto parsedModifier = Inspector::Protocol::AutomationHelpers::parseEnumValueFromString<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyModifier>(modifierString);
1771 if (!parsedModifier)
1772 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "A modifier in the 'modifiers' array is invalid.");
1773
1774 keyModifiers.add(protocolModifierToWebEventModifier(parsedModifier.value()));
1775 }
1776
1777 page->getWindowFrameWithCallback([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback), page = makeRef(*page), floatX, floatY, mouseInteraction, mouseButton, keyModifiers](WebCore::FloatRect windowFrame) mutable {
1778 floatX = std::min(std::max(0.0f, floatX), windowFrame.size().width());
1779 floatY = std::min(std::max(0.0f, floatY), windowFrame.size().height());
1780
1781 WebCore::IntPoint locationInViewport = WebCore::IntPoint(static_cast<int>(floatX), static_cast<int>(floatY));
1782
1783 auto mouseEventsFlushedCallback = [protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), callback = WTFMove(callback), page, floatX, floatY](std::optional<AutomationCommandError> error) {
1784 if (error)
1785 callback->sendFailure(error.value().toProtocolString());
1786 else {
1787 callback->sendSuccess(Inspector::Protocol::Automation::Point::create()
1788 .setX(floatX)
1789 .setY(floatY - page->topContentInset())
1790 .release());
1791 }
1792 };
1793
1794 auto& callbackInMap = m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.add(page->identifier(), nullptr).iterator->value;
1795 if (callbackInMap)
1796 callbackInMap(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(Timeout));
1797 callbackInMap = WTFMove(mouseEventsFlushedCallback);
1798
1799 platformSimulateMouseInteraction(page, mouseInteraction, mouseButton, locationInViewport, keyModifiers, WebCore::mousePointerEventType());
1800
1801 // If the event location was previously clipped and does not hit test anything in the window, then it will not be processed.
1802 // For compatibility with pre-W3C driver implementations, don't make this a hard error; just do nothing silently.
1803 // In W3C-only code paths, we can reject any pointer actions whose coordinates are outside the viewport rect.
1804 if (callbackInMap && !page->isProcessingMouseEvents()) {
1805 auto callbackToCancel = m_pendingMouseEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.take(page->identifier());
1806 callbackToCancel(std::nullopt);
1807 }
1808 });
1809#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_MOUSE_INTERACTIONS)
1810}
1811
1812void WebAutomationSession::performKeyboardInteractions(const Inspector::Protocol::Automation::BrowsingContextHandle& handle, Ref<JSON::Array>&& interactions, Ref<PerformKeyboardInteractionsCallback>&& callback)
1813{
1814#if !ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
1815 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(NotImplemented);
1816#else
1817 WebPageProxy* page = webPageProxyForHandle(handle);
1818 if (!page)
1819 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR(WindowNotFound);
1820
1821 if (!interactions->length())
1822 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "The parameter 'interactions' was not found or empty.");
1823
1824 // Validate all of the parameters before performing any interactions with the browsing context under test.
1825 Vector<WTF::Function<void()>> actionsToPerform;
1826 actionsToPerform.reserveCapacity(interactions->length());
1827
1828 for (const auto& interactionValue : interactions.get()) {
1829 auto interactionObject = interactionValue->asObject();
1830 if (!interactionObject)
1831 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "An interaction in the 'interactions' parameter was invalid.");
1832
1833 auto interactionTypeString = interactionObject->getString("type"_s);
1834 if (!interactionTypeString)
1835 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "An interaction in the 'interactions' parameter is missing the 'type' key.");
1836 auto interactionType = Inspector::Protocol::AutomationHelpers::parseEnumValueFromString<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyboardInteractionType>(interactionTypeString);
1837 if (!interactionType)
1838 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "An interaction in the 'interactions' parameter has an invalid 'type' key.");
1839
1840 auto virtualKeyString = interactionObject->getString("key"_s);
1841 if (!!virtualKeyString) {
1842 std::optional<VirtualKey> virtualKey = Inspector::Protocol::AutomationHelpers::parseEnumValueFromString<Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey>(virtualKeyString);
1843 if (!virtualKey)
1844 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "An interaction in the 'interactions' parameter has an invalid 'key' value.");
1845
1846 actionsToPerform.uncheckedAppend([this, page, interactionType, virtualKey] {
1847 platformSimulateKeyboardInteraction(*page, interactionType.value(), virtualKey.value());
1848 });
1849 }
1850
1851 auto keySequence = interactionObject->getString("text"_s);
1852 if (!!keySequence) {
1853 switch (interactionType.value()) {
1854 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyboardInteractionType::KeyPress:
1855 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyboardInteractionType::KeyRelease:
1856 // 'KeyPress' and 'KeyRelease' are meant for a virtual key and are not supported for a string (sequence of codepoints).
1857 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InvalidParameter, "An interaction in the 'interactions' parameter has an invalid 'key' value.");
1858
1859 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::KeyboardInteractionType::InsertByKey:
1860 actionsToPerform.uncheckedAppend([this, page, keySequence] {
1861 platformSimulateKeySequence(*page, keySequence);
1862 });
1863 break;
1864 }
1865 }
1866
1867 if (!virtualKeyString && !keySequence)
1868 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(MissingParameter, "An interaction in the 'interactions' parameter is missing both 'key' and 'text'. One must be provided.");
1869 }
1870
1871 ASSERT(actionsToPerform.size());
1872 if (!actionsToPerform.size())
1873 ASYNC_FAIL_WITH_PREDEFINED_ERROR_AND_DETAILS(InternalError, "No actions to perform.");
1874
1875 auto keyboardEventsFlushedCallback = [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback), page = makeRef(*page)](std::optional<AutomationCommandError> error) {
1876 if (error)
1877 callback->sendFailure(error.value().toProtocolString());
1878 else
1879 callback->sendSuccess();
1880 };
1881
1882 auto& callbackInMap = m_pendingKeyboardEventsFlushedCallbacksPerPage.add(page->identifier(), nullptr).iterator->value;
1883 if (callbackInMap)
1884 callbackInMap(AUTOMATION_COMMAND_ERROR_WITH_NAME(Timeout));
1885 callbackInMap = WTFMove(keyboardEventsFlushedCallback);
1886
1887 for (auto& action : actionsToPerform)
1888 action();
1889#endif // ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_KEYBOARD_INTERACTIONS)
1890}

1892#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_ACTIONS_API)
1893static SimulatedInputSourceType simulatedInputSourceTypeFromProtocolSourceType(Inspector::Protocol::Automation::InputSourceType protocolType)
1894{
1895 switch (protocolType) {
1896 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::InputSourceType::Null:
1897 return SimulatedInputSourceType::Null;
1898 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::InputSourceType::Keyboard:
1899 return SimulatedInputSourceType::Keyboard;
1900 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::InputSourceType::Mouse:
1901 return SimulatedInputSourceType::Mouse;
1902 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::InputSourceType::Touch:
1903 return SimulatedInputSourceType::Touch;
1904 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::InputSourceType::Wheel:
1905 return SimulatedInputSourceType::Wheel;

1914#if ENABLE(WEBDRIVER_ACTIONS_API)
1915// ยง15.4.2 Keyboard actions
1916// https://w3c.github.io/webdriver/#dfn-normalised-key-value
1917static VirtualKey normalizedVirtualKey(VirtualKey key)
1918{
1919 switch (key) {
1920 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::ControlRight:
1921 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::Control;
1922 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::ShiftRight:
1923 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::Shift;
1924 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::AlternateRight:
1925 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::Alternate;
1926 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::MetaRight:
1927 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::Meta;
1928 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::DownArrowRight:
1929 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::DownArrow;
1930 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::UpArrowRight:
1931 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::UpArrow;
1932 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::LeftArrowRight:
1933 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::LeftArrow;
1934 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::RightArrowRight:
1935 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::RightArrow;
1936 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::PageUpRight:
1937 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::PageUp;
1938 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::PageDownRight:
1939 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::PageDown;
1940 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::EndRight:
1941 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::End;
1942 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::HomeRight:
1943 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::Home;
1944 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::DeleteRight:
1945 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::Delete;
1946 case Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::InsertRight:
1947 return Inspector::Protocol::Automation::VirtualKey::Insert;
1948 default:
1949 return key;
1950 }
1951}
1952
1953static std::optional<UChar32> pressedCharKey(const String& pressedCharKeyString)
1954{
1955 switch (pressedCharKeyString.length()) {
1956 case 1:
1957 return pressedCharKeyString.characterAt(0);
1958 case 2: {
1959 auto lead = pressedCharKeyString.characterAt(0);
1960 auto trail = pressedCharKeyString.characterAt(1);
1961 if (U16_IS_LEAD(lead) && U16_IS_TRAIL(trail))
1962 return U16_GET_SUPPLEMENTARY(lead, trail);
1963 }
1964 }
1965
1966 return std::nullopt;
1967}
